Reno Omokri has commended President Muhammad Buhari for signing the Electoral Bill 2022 into law. Buhari had earlier today signed the bill into law. The development has continued to trigger reactions from concerned Nigerians who expressed hope that the new electoral system would enhance better governance. Reacting to this in a post on his verified Facebook page, Omokri said the development is an indicator that the president is committed to democracy. UK Bans Russian Airlines From Entering British Airspace, Russia… Joe Biden To Nominate Ketanji Brown Jackson For US Supreme Court He said, “I commend General Buhari for signing the Electoral Act into law. By this act, General Buhari has shown commitment to democracy. Buhari has taken a number of irresponsible decisions over the years, of which I opposed him. But in this, he deserves kudos! “And if General Buhari continues along these lines, all he will get from me is praise. But if he deviates, then my table shaking will continue.” The socio-political activist, however, advised the president to do more by building hospitals for himself and Nigerians which would stop politicians from foreign medical trips. “Stay in Nigeria. Build hospitals for yourself and Nigerians, especially Nigerians who urinate in public, and I will not embarrass you with #HarassTinubuOutofLondon”, he added.